316 static Triple::ArchType parseBPFArch(StringRef ArchName) { 0
317 if (ArchName.equals("bpf")) { 0
318 if (sys::IsLittleEndianHost) ----
319 return Triple::bpfel; 0
320 else ----
321 return Triple::bpfeb; ----
322 } else if (ArchName.equals("bpf_be") || ArchName.equals("bpfeb")) { 0
323 return Triple::bpfeb; 0
324 } else if (ArchName.equals("bpf_le") || ArchName.equals("bpfel")) { 0
325 return Triple::bpfel; 0
326 } else { ----
327 return Triple::UnknownArch; 0
328 } ----
329 } ----

402 static Triple::ArchType parseARMArch(StringRef ArchName) { 0
403 ARM::ISAKind ISA = ARM::parseArchISA(ArchName); 0
404 ARM::EndianKind ENDIAN = ARM::parseArchEndian(ArchName); 0
405 ----
406 Triple::ArchType arch = Triple::UnknownArch; 0
407 switch (ENDIAN) { 0
408 case ARM::EndianKind::LITTLE: { 0
409 switch (ISA) { ----
410 case ARM::ISAKind::ARM: 0
411 arch = Triple::arm; 0
412 break; 0
413 case ARM::ISAKind::THUMB: 0
414 arch = Triple::thumb; 0
415 break; 0
416 case ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64: 0
417 arch = Triple::aarch64; 0
418 break; 0
419 case ARM::ISAKind::INVALID: 0
420 break; 0
421 } ----
422 break; 0
423 } ----
424 case ARM::EndianKind::BIG: { 0
425 switch (ISA) { ----
426 case ARM::ISAKind::ARM: 0
427 arch = Triple::armeb; 0
428 break; 0
429 case ARM::ISAKind::THUMB: 0
430 arch = Triple::thumbeb; 0
431 break; 0
432 case ARM::ISAKind::AARCH64: 0
433 arch = Triple::aarch64_be; 0
434 break; 0
435 case ARM::ISAKind::INVALID: 0
436 break; 0
437 } ----
438 break; 0
439 } ----
440 case ARM::EndianKind::INVALID: { 0
441 break; 0
442 } ----
443 } ----
444 ----
445 ArchName = ARM::getCanonicalArchName(ArchName); 0
446 if (ArchName.empty()) 0
447 return Triple::UnknownArch; 0
448 ----
449 // Thumb only exists in v4+ ----
450 if (ISA == ARM::ISAKind::THUMB && 0
451 (ArchName.startswith("v2") || ArchName.startswith("v3"))) 0
452 return Triple::UnknownArch; 0
453 ----
454 // Thumb only for v6m ----
455 ARM::ProfileKind Profile = ARM::parseArchProfile(ArchName); 0
456 unsigned Version = ARM::parseArchVersion(ArchName); 0
457 if (Profile == ARM::ProfileKind::M && Version == 6) { 0
458 if (ENDIAN == ARM::EndianKind::BIG) 0
459 return Triple::thumbeb; 0
460 else ----
461 return Triple::thumb; 0
462 } ----
463 ----
464 return arch; 0
465 } ----

1225 bool Triple::getMacOSXVersion(VersionTuple &Version) const { 0
1226 Version = getOSVersion(); 0
1227 ----
1228 switch (getOS()) { 0

1230 case Darwin: 0

1235 if (Version.getMajor() < 4) { 0

1237 } ----

1252 break; 0

1257 // the clang driver combines OS X and IOS support into a common Darwin ----

1259 // IOS. ----
1260 Version = VersionTuple(10, 4); 0
1261 break; 0
1262 case DriverKit: 0
1263 llvm_unreachable("OSX version isn't relevant for DriverKit"); 0
1264 } ----

1266 } ----
